This analysis detects possible double-free of the same allocation.
1. Identify first free and potential second free sites.
2. Confirm both frees can target the same allocation/alias.
3. Are the frees on mutually exclusive control-flow paths?
4. Is pointer invalidation (for example set to null or reassigned) guaranteed before second free?
Use the tools to trace aliasing and path feasibility.
If only one free is reachable per allocation, there is no issue.
Only flag if two frees of the same allocation are reachable.
